creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 138 by Various.
Read in English by Shakira Searle; Chris Pyle; Thomas A. Copeland; Winston Tharp; Bruce Kachuk; Ed Humpal; Rosslyn Carlyle; John N. Daily; SuperCoconut; Phil Schempf; Leonard Wilson; Olivereading; Christopher Dudley; Son of the Exiles
This is a collection of 25 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for November 2014.
This collection includes the following: Sonnet VI: Bluebeard, by Edna St. Vincent Millay The Corpse, by Charles Baudelaire The Enduring, by John Gould Fletcher The Flaming Heart, by Richard Crashaw In the Desert, by Stephen Crane In The Study, by Thomas Hardy Ode: Intimations of Immortality from Recollections of Early Childhood, by William Wordsworth Kaare's Song, by Bjørnstjerne Bjørnson Lament of the Winds, by Archibald Lampman We Have A Little Garden, by Beatrix Potter On first looking into Chapman’s Homer, by John Keats Lying, by Thomas Moore No!, by Thomas Hood Orkney Lullaby, by Eugene Field The Power of the Dog, by Rudyard Kipling Rural Bliss, by Anthony Charles Deane She Charged Me, by Thomas Hardy Sittin on the Porch, by Edgar A. Guest This Living Hand, by John Keats To A Portrait, by Arthur Symons Upon Westminster Bridge, by William Wordsworth When I Was King, by Henry Lawson When the Year Grows Old, by Edna St. Vincent Millay Whispers of immortality, by T. S. Eliot The Wound-Dresser, by Walt Whitman For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
